Write a program in a class named Shining that prints the following line of output 1000 times:

All work and no play makes Jack a dull boy.

You should not write a program whose source code is 1000 lines long; use methods to shorten the program. What is the shortest 
program you can write that will produce the 1000 lines of output, using only the material from Chapter 1 (println, methods, 
etc.)?

-----------------------------------------------------------
Type your solution here:

public class Shining {
	public static void main(String[] args) {
		printFiveHundred();
		printFiveHundred();	
	}
	public static void printFiveHundred() {
		printHundred();
		printHundred();
		printHundred();
		printHundred();
		printHundred();
	}
	public static void printHundred() {
		printTowenty();
		printTowenty();
		printTowenty();
		printTowenty();
		printTowenty();
	}
    public static void printTowenty() {
        printFive();
        printFive();
        printFive();
        printFive();
    }
    public static void printFive() {
        System.out.println("All work and no play makes Jack a dull boy.");
        System.out.println("All work and no play makes Jack a dull boy.");
        System.out.println("All work and no play makes Jack a dull boy.");
        System.out.println("All work and no play makes Jack a dull boy.");
        System.out.println("All work and no play makes Jack a dull boy.");
    }
}
